## 7. Internal SOP (Provider/Admin Only)

### SOP — HubSpot Marketing Hub: Setup & Configuration

**Knowledgeable worker:** Thorstein Nordby  
**System type:** Marketing / HubSpot  
**System interval:** Triggered (new HubSpot portal, rebuild, or major marketing change)

This SOP defines **how** Marketing Hub onboarding is executed internally.  
It is **never visible to customers**.

---

### SOP Sections (Internal, Full)

#### 1. File Manager Setup
- Navigate to Marketing → Files
- Create folder structure:
  - `brand`
    - `logo`
    - `svg`
    - `png`
    - `jpg`
    - `fonts`
    - `favicon`
  - `campaigns`
  - `video`
  - `images`
  - `scripts`
- Upload all brand assets to correct folders

---

#### 2. Data Privacy & Consent
- Navigate to Privacy / Consent settings
- Configure consent banner:
  - Design and placement
  - Cookie and data usage text
  - Cookie preference options
  - Geo-based display rules (if required)
- Integrate tracking scripts correctly
- Ensure accessibility compliance
- Include link to Privacy Policy
- Test on desktop and mobile
- Publish to live site

---

#### 3. Email Subscription Types
- Navigate to Marketing → Email → Subscription Types
- Create required subscription types
- Add name and description
- Configure data privacy messaging (if enabled)
- Select communication method
- Reorder subscription types logically
- Add translations for international contacts if needed

---

#### 4. Domains & Subdomains
- Navigate to Website → Domains & URLs
- Connect required domains and subdomains
- Configure:
  - Primary vs secondary domains
  - Redirect rules
  - SSL provisioning
- Validate DNS records with IT or provider
- Confirm domain health

---

#### 5. Forms
- Create:
  - Newsletter signup form
  - Contact form
  - Request demo / talk to sales form
- Configure:
  - Required fields
  - GDPR options
  - Notifications
  - Redirects / thank-you messages
- Test submissions end-to-end

---

#### 6. Calls-to-Action (CTAs)
- Create core CTAs (button/image)
- Configure destination links
- Set display rules
- Preview and publish
- Monitor basic analytics

---

#### 7. Email Marketing Templates
- Create base email template
- Configure branding, fonts, and layout
- Enable tracking
- Test on desktop and mobile

---

#### 8. Landing Page Templates
- Select appropriate template type (starter/theme/custom)
- Configure:
  - SEO defaults
  - Language
  - Featured images
- Publish and validate rendering
- Test responsiveness

---

#### 9. Design Manager & Fonts
- Upload custom font files to Files
- Add `@font-face` rules in Design Manager stylesheet
- Apply fonts via CSS
- Validate usage across templates

---

#### 10. Advertising Channels
- Connect ad accounts (Google, LinkedIn, Meta if applicable)
- Authorize access
- Configure attribution and tracking
- Validate sync

---

#### 11. Social Media Accounts
- Connect social channels
- Configure posting permissions
- Validate analytics connection

---

#### 12. Marketing Workflows
- Create workflow folder structure:
  - Data governance
  - Deal automation
  - Marketing
  - Operations
  - Archive
- Implement governance and lifecycle workflows
- Test enrollments and actions

---

#### 13. Reporting & Dashboards
- Create marketing dashboards
- Configure core KPIs
- Validate filters and date ranges
- Share dashboards with stakeholders

---

